e U.S. men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s medley relay, with the dethroning delivered by a Chinese team dogged by doping controversies.\", \"from\": 438, \"to\": 618, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 574, \"end\": 581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.8699207443208274, \"rank\": 0.14711147425444568, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic-history\", \"from\": 483, \"to\": 498}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 516}, {\"ngram\": \"men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s medley relay\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 537}, {\"ngram\": \"the dethroning\", \"from\": 544, \"to\": 558}, {\"ngram\": \"doping controversies\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 617}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And then that gave way to a powerful, walk-off world record by the American women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s medley relay.\", \"from\": 619, \"to\": 718, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 686, \"end\": 694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999153051284, \"rank\": 6.461485262990994e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"way\", \"from\": 638, \"to\": 641}, {\"ngram\": \"a powerful, walk-off world record\", \"from\": 645, \"to\": 678}, {\"ngram\": \"women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 695, \"to\": 704}, {\"ngram\": \"medley relay\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 717}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fin, as they say in French.\", \"from\": 720, \"to\": 747, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 740, \"end\": 746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9180740096594473, \"rank\": 0.07701175237372415, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Fin\", \"from\": 720, \"to\": 723}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now the reckoning begins.\", \"from\": 749, \"to\": 774, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the reckoning\", \"from\": 753, \"to\": 766}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The final day was an appropriate mixed bag of results for a wildly uneven, largely disappointing U.S. performance.\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 890, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The final day\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 789}, {\"ngram\": \"an appropriate mixed bag\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 818}, {\"ngram\": \"results\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 829}, {\"ngram\": \"a wildly uneven, largely disappointing U.S. performance\", \"from\": 834, \"to\": 889}]}, {\"sentence\": \"USA Swimming can point to winning both the gold medal and overall medal tallies, with eight golds and 28 total medals to Australia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s seven golds and 18 total medals.\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 1058, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 891, \"end\": 903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USA Swimming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"both the gold medal\", \"from\": 925, \"to\": 944}, {\"ngram\": \"overall medal tallies\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 970}, {\"ngram\": \"eight golds\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 988}, {\"ngram\": \"28 total medals\", \"from\": 993, \"to\": 1008}, {\"ngram\": \"Australia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s seven golds\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"18 total medals\", \"from\": 1042, \"to\": 1057}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After losing the gold-medal tally 13-7 to the Aussies at World Championships last year,\\u00c2 that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s at least one embarrassment reversed.\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1194, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the gold-medal tally\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1092}, {\"ngram\": \"the Aussies\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1112}, {\"ngram\": \"World Championships\", \"from\": 1116, \"to\": 1135}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2\", \"from\": 1146, \"to\": 1147}, {\"ngram\": \"at least one embarrassment\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1183}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barely.\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1202, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But here\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the bigger picture: eight golds is the fewest by the Americans in the pool since 1988, and the 28 total is the fewest since 2004.\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1346, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the bigger picture\", \"from\": 1217, \"to\": 1235}, {\"ngram\": \"eight golds\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1248}, {\"ngram\": \"the Americans\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1279}, {\"ngram\": \"the pool\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1291}, {\"ngram\": \"the 28 total\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1320}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And keep in mind, three events and nine medal chances have been added since 2020.\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1428, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"mind\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1363}, {\"ngram\": \"three events\", \"from\": 1365, \"to\": 1377}, {\"ngram\": \"nine medal chances\", \"from\": 1382, \"to\": 1400}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nobody expected this to be an easy swimming Olympics for the country that has historically dominated.\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1531, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Nobody\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1436}, {\"ngram\": \"an easy swimming Olympics\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1482}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1498}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But hopes were raised after a fast performance at U.S. Olympic trials in June in Indianapolis, and then the Americans failed to follow through in France.\", \"from\": 1532, \"to\": 1685, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1613, \"end\": 1625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"score\": 0.614095385622736, \"rank\": 0.5663943885137503, \"text\": \"Indianapolis\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\"}, {\"begin\": 1678, \"end\": 1684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.7845500437796276, \"rank\": 0.26815250413558067, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"hopes\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 1541}, {\"ngram\": \"a fast performance\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1578}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. Olympic trials\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1601}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 1605, \"to\": 1609}, {\"ngram\": \"the Americans\", \"from\": 1636, \"to\": 1649}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Times are difficult to compare from Indy to now because of the La D\\u00c3\\u00a9fense Arena pool, which produced a lot ofslow performances and some erratic results.\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1840, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Times\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1692}, {\"ngram\": \"Indy\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1727}, {\"ngram\": \"the La D\\u00c3\\u00a9fense Arena pool\", \"from\": 1746, \"to\": 1772}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot ofslow performances\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 1814}, {\"ngram\": \"some erratic results\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1839}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Place matters more than time at the Olympics anyway, and in general the U.S. did not swim up to its seeding.\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1949, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Place\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1846}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 1865, \"to\": 1869}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1873, \"to\": 1885}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 1917}, {\"ngram\": \"its seeding\", \"from\": 1937, \"to\": 1948}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Across 35 events, American swimmers finished a combined 89 places lower than their seeding on the pre-meet entry list\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094an average drop of 2.5 spots.\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 2100, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1969, \"end\": 1977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999153051284, \"rank\": 6.461485262990994e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"35 events\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 1967}, {\"ngram\": \"a combined 89 places\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2016}, {\"ngram\": \"their seeding\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2041}, {\"ngram\": \"the pre-meet entry list\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094an average drop\", \"from\": 2045, \"to\": 2086}, {\"ngram\": \"2.5 spots\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2099}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women fared considerably better than the men in that regard, while also winning five golds to the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s two (one was shared in the mixed medley relay).\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2258, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The women\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2110}, {\"ngram\": \"the men\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2149}, {\"ngram\": \"that regard\", \"from\": 2153, \"to\": 2164}, {\"ngram\": \"five golds\", \"from\": 2185, \"to\": 2195}, {\"ngram\": \"the mixed medley relay\", \"from\": 2234, \"to\": 2256}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A few extreme busts skew the seeding number slightly, when other metrics make the overall performance look slightly less drastic.\", \"from\": 2260, \"to\": 2389, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A few extreme busts\", \"from\": 2260, \"to\": 2279}, {\"ngram\": \"the seeding number\", \"from\": 2285, \"to\": 2303}, {\"ngram\": \"other metrics\", \"from\": 2319, \"to\": 2332}, {\"ngram\": \"the overall performance\", \"from\": 2338, \"to\": 2361}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance, five times Americans were seeded to win medals and missed the podium, while three Americans took home hardware who were not expected to, according to seeding.\", \"from\": 2390, \"to\": 2562, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"instance\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2402}, {\"ngram\": \"Americans\", \"from\": 2415, \"to\": 2424}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 2444, \"to\": 2450}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 2462, \"to\": 2472}, {\"ngram\": \"three Americans\", \"from\": 2480, \"to\": 2495}, {\"ngram\": \"home hardware\", \"from\": 2501, \"to\": 2514}, {\"ngram\": \"seeding\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2561}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, the overall picture of underperformance is pretty clear, and the sky-high U.S. standards don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t allow for much in the way of underperforming.\", \"from\": 2564, \"to\": 2713, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the overall picture\", \"from\": 2571, \"to\": 2590}, {\"ngram\": \"underperformance\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2610}, {\"ngram\": \"the sky-high U.S. standards\", \"from\": 2632, \"to\": 2659}, {\"ngram\": \"don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t\", \"from\": 2660, \"to\": 2667}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 2686, \"to\": 2693}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimming might only be second to basketball in terms of the public demand to dominate at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2816, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Swimming\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2722}, {\"ngram\": \"basketball\", \"from\": 2747, \"to\": 2757}, {\"ngram\": \"terms\", \"from\": 2761, \"to\": 2766}, {\"ngram\": \"the public demand\", \"from\": 2770, \"to\": 2787}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2803, \"to\": 2815}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American male headliner Caeleb Dressel, who bounced back from a two-event debacle Friday to swim a very good butterfly leg on the medley relay, spoke two truths that are in conflict with each other: the standards aren\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t changing in the U.S. and the world is catching up.\", \"from\": 2818, \"to\": 3090, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2818, \"end\": 2826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999153051284, \"rank\": 6.461485262990994e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2842, \"end\": 2856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caeleb Dressel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a two-event debacle\", \"from\": 2880, \"to\": 2899}, {\"ngram\": \"a very good butterfly leg\", \"from\": 2915, \"to\": 2940}, {\"ngram\": \"the medley relay\", \"from\": 2944, \"to\": 2960}, {\"ngram\": \"two truths\", \"from\": 2968, \"to\": 2978}, {\"ngram\": \"conflict\", \"from\": 2991, \"to\": 2999}, {\"ngram\": \"the standards\", \"from\": 3017, \"to\": 3030}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 3052, \"to\": 3060}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3065, \"to\": 3074}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t a bad meet at all,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said Dressel, who has won nine Olympic medals, eight of them gold.\", \"from\": 3092, \"to\": 3195, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\", \"from\": 3125, \"to\": 3128}, {\"ngram\": \"Dressel\", \"from\": 3134, \"to\": 3141}, {\"ngram\": \"nine Olympic medals\", \"from\": 3155, \"to\": 3174}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe goal when you come to the Olympics and World Championships is gold medals.\", \"from\": 3196, \"to\": 3277, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe goal\", \"from\": 3196, \"to\": 3207}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3225, \"to\": 3237}, {\"ngram\": \"World Championships\", \"from\": 3242, \"to\": 3261}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medals\", \"from\": 3265, \"to\": 3276}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s other countries that are getting very dominant.\", \"from\": 3278, \"to\": 3335, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s other countries\", \"from\": 3278, \"to\": 3303}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The wealth has just been spread around.\", \"from\": 3336, \"to\": 3375, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The wealth\", \"from\": 3336, \"to\": 3346}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t think we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re getting any worse, per se.\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t think the goals need to change because the world is getting faster.\\u00c2 I don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t think we start striving for silver and bronze\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094not that there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s anything wrong with that, but we want to be the most dominant team.\", \"from\": 3376, \"to\": 3656, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re\", \"from\": 3392, \"to\": 3399}, {\"ngram\": \"the goals\", \"from\": 3447, \"to\": 3456}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3480, \"to\": 3489}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 3548, \"to\": 3554}, {\"ngram\": \"there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3586}, {\"ngram\": \"the most dominant team\", \"from\": 3631, \"to\": 3653}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And we were at these Games.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d The margins were just smaller.\", \"from\": 3657, \"to\": 3719, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The margins\", \"from\": 3688, \"to\": 3699}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And truth be told, the U.S. went into the weekend needing to swim very well to salvage anything positive from this meet.\", \"from\": 3720, \"to\": 3840, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"truth\", \"from\": 3724, \"to\": 3729}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 3739, \"to\": 3747}, {\"ngram\": \"the weekend\", \"from\": 3758, \"to\": 3769}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 3807, \"to\": 3815}, {\"ngram\": \"this meet\", \"from\": 3830, \"to\": 3839}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That largely happened.\", \"from\": 3842, \"to\": 3864, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On SaturdayKatie Ledecky did what she does, winning the 800 freestyle, and then the mixed medley relay came through.\", \"from\": 3865, \"to\": 3981, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"SaturdayKatie Ledecky\", \"from\": 3868, \"to\": 3889}, {\"ngram\": \"the 800 freestyle\", \"from\": 3917, \"to\": 3934}, {\"ngram\": \"the mixed medley relay\", \"from\": 3945, \"to\": 3967}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And on Sunday, Finke and the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s relay sandwiched some heroics around another otherworldly Chinese performance.\", \"from\": 3982, \"to\": 4099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4079, \"end\": 4086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.8699207443208274, \"rank\": 0.14711147425444568, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 3989, \"to\": 3995}, {\"ngram\": \"Finke\", \"from\": 3997, \"to\": 4002}, {\"ngram\": \"the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s relay\", \"from\": 4007, \"to\": 4026}, {\"ngram\": \"some heroics\", \"from\": 4038, \"to\": 4050}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Leading up to his race, Finke was well aware ofAmerica\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s no-gold individual performance by the men.\", \"from\": 4101, \"to\": 4202, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his race\", \"from\": 4115, \"to\": 4123}, {\"ngram\": \"Finke\", \"from\": 4125, \"to\": 4130}, {\"ngram\": \"no-gold individual performance\", \"from\": 4160, \"to\": 4190}, {\"ngram\": \"the men\", \"from\": 4194, \"to\": 4201}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not one to shy away from what many athletes would call \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009coutside noise\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he said he actually dove into the comments section on the niche website Swimswam.com.\", \"from\": 4203, \"to\": 4363, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many athletes\", \"from\": 4233, \"to\": 4246}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009coutside\", \"from\": 4258, \"to\": 4268}, {\"ngram\": \"noise\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\", \"from\": 4269, \"to\": 4277}, {\"ngram\": \"the comments section\", \"from\": 4308, \"to\": 4328}, {\"ngram\": \"the niche website\", \"from\": 4332, \"to\": 4349}, {\"ngram\": \"Swimswam.com\", \"from\": 4350, \"to\": 4362}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI like reading that stuff,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Finke said.\", \"from\": 4365, \"to\": 4409, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that stuff\", \"from\": 4383, \"to\": 4393}, {\"ngram\": \"Finke\", \"from\": 4398, \"to\": 4403}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt kind of motivates me inside.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d That said, Finke also acknowledged feeling pressure.\", \"from\": 4410, \"to\": 4501, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\", \"from\": 4410, \"to\": 4415}, {\"ngram\": \"Finke\", \"from\": 4459, \"to\": 4464}, {\"ngram\": \"feeling pressure\", \"from\": 4483, \"to\": 4499}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After winning both the 800 and 1,500 in Tokyo three years ago, he couldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t quite rally to catch Ireland\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Daniel Wiffen in the shorter of the two races earlier in the week.\", \"from\": 4502, \"to\": 4678, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4542, \"end\": 4547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999969350029, \"rank\": 3.065163984415215e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Daniel Wiffen\", \"from\": 4612, \"to\": 4625}, {\"ngram\": \"the two races\", \"from\": 4644, \"to\": 4657}, {\"ngram\": \"the week\", \"from\": 4669, \"to\": 4677}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So he got on the blocks for the 1,500 and just went for it.\", \"from\": 4679, \"to\": 4738, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the blocks\", \"from\": 4692, \"to\": 4702}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a scary strategy in the longest pool race, one that can come at a heavy cost.\", \"from\": 4740, \"to\": 4826, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a scary strategy\", \"from\": 4740, \"to\": 4765}, {\"ngram\": \"the longest pool race\", \"from\": 4769, \"to\": 4790}, {\"ngram\": \"a heavy cost\", \"from\": 4813, \"to\": 4825}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And it runs counter to Finke\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s trademark, late-charging style.\", \"from\": 4827, \"to\": 4891, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Finke\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s trademark\", \"from\": 4850, \"to\": 4869}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But with everything on the line he just tossed aside caution and attacked from the very first stroke.\", \"from\": 4892, \"to\": 4993, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 4901, \"to\": 4911}, {\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 4915, \"to\": 4923}, {\"ngram\": \"caution\", \"from\": 4945, \"to\": 4952}, {\"ngram\": \"the very first stroke\", \"from\": 4971, \"to\": 4992}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThat really was not my strategy going into the race,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he acknowledged with a laugh.\", \"from\": 4995, \"to\": 5083, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThat\", \"from\": 4995, \"to\": 5002}, {\"ngram\": \"my strategy\", \"from\": 5018, \"to\": 5029}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 5041, \"to\": 5049}, {\"ngram\": \"a laugh\", \"from\": 5075, \"to\": 5082}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t know how the race was going to play out.\", \"from\": 5084, \"to\": 5138, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\", \"from\": 5084, \"to\": 5088}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 5107, \"to\": 5115}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I kind of saw I had a pretty decent lead at the 300 so I knew I had to keep going and make the guys hurt a little bit.\", \"from\": 5139, \"to\": 5257, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a pretty decent lead\", \"from\": 5159, \"to\": 5179}, {\"ngram\": \"the guys\", \"from\": 5230, \"to\": 5238}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They started to catch up to me and I was getting a little worried, so I knew I had to keep pushing.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Wiffen and, more pertinently, Italy\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Gregorio Paltrinieri, were the ones trying to catch Finke.\", \"from\": 5258, \"to\": 5460, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"pushing.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Wiffen\", \"from\": 5349, \"to\": 5367}, {\"ngram\": \"the ones\", \"from\": 5428, \"to\": 5436}, {\"ngram\": \"Finke\", \"from\": 5453, \"to\": 5458}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While his lead was getting smaller, his pace ahead of world-record time was getting larger.\", \"from\": 5461, \"to\": 5552, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his lead\", \"from\": 5467, \"to\": 5475}, {\"ngram\": \"smaller, his pace\", \"from\": 5488, \"to\": 5505}, {\"ngram\": \"world-record time\", \"from\": 5515, \"to\": 5532}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The crowd got behind Finke\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s record pursuit in the latter stages.\", \"from\": 5553, \"to\": 5620, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The crowd\", \"from\": 5553, \"to\": 5562}, {\"ngram\": \"Finke\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s record pursuit\", \"from\": 5574, \"to\": 5598}, {\"ngram\": \"the latter stages\", \"from\": 5602, \"to\": 5619}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Finke was only concerned with finishing first, trying to complete the transformation from a dead closer to a front-runner.\", \"from\": 5622, \"to\": 5748, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Finke\", \"from\": 5626, \"to\": 5631}, {\"ngram\": \"the transformation\", \"from\": 5692, \"to\": 5710}, {\"ngram\": \"a front-runner\", \"from\": 5733, \"to\": 5747}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t let go of this now,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he thought to himself.\", \"from\": 5750, \"to\": 5808, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t be the guy who got run down after I do all the running down.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d He ran away instead, scoring the last 50 in trademark Finke fashion to break the 12-year-old world record of China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Sun Yang.\", \"from\": 5809, \"to\": 6015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6006, \"end\": 6014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun_Yang\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sun Yang\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun_Yang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun_Yang\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the guy\", \"from\": 5825, \"to\": 5832}, {\"ngram\": \"trademark Finke fashion\", \"from\": 5930, \"to\": 5953}, {\"ngram\": \"the 12-year-old world record\", \"from\": 5963, \"to\": 5991}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the whack-a-mole game of China and drug testing, removing the controversial Sun from the record books\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s served a drug suspension and been involved in testing brouhahas\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094was followed minutes later by that country winning the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s medley.\", \"from\": 6016, \"to\": 6266, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6044, \"end\": 6049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999987267818972, \"rank\": 1.212293716947397e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wik